			<title>Reentry Job Training, Social Entrepreneurism at Work at Boaz & Ruth</title>

				<meta name="keywords" content="systemic issues, prisoner reentry, recidivism, community revitalization, cross-cultural, job training, released prisoners, community revitalization, rebuild, community, entrepreneurial, cross-cultural connection, Cultural Bridges, collaborative partnerships, criminal justice, government agencies, academic communities, social entrepreneurs">

				<meta name="description" content="Boaz & Ruth is a non-profit, faith-based initiative that uses innovative social entrepreneurism to craft a program designed to bridge the gap between those who possess wealth and privilege and those who do not.  Focusing on systemic issues of prisoner re-entry, community revitalization and cross-cultural connection, Boaz and Ruth is making an impact on the city of Richmond, Virginia and beyond.">
